Expected Information Gain Doctrine

Abbreviation: EIG
Domain: Pantheon Physics / R&D / Semantic Observatory / Luck Engine

Core Principle

Seek the action that teaches the most valuable truth per unit cost.

Purpose

EIG ranks what Pantheon should investigate next when multiple paths are possible.

It converts curiosity into strategy.

Canonical Formula

EIG = Expected uncertainty reduction × Mission value × Leverage
      -------------------------------------------------------
                 Cost × Risk × Time

Plain Meaning

A good target is one that:

* reduces uncertainty
* matters to the mission
* unlocks other work
* costs little enough to test
* carries acceptable risk
* can be learned from quickly

Operator

Observe uncertainty
      ↓
Estimate value
      ↓
Estimate cost / risk / time
      ↓
Rank possible probes
      ↓
Test highest EIG target
      ↓
Archive result
      ↓
Update coordinates

